ns1:Requirement.ns1:Description: [In Messages] In the following [section 2] sections, the schema definition might differ from the processing rules imposed by the protocol.
[In Messages] The WSDL in this specification [MS-OXWSCONT] provides a base description of the protocol.
[In Messages] The schema in this specification [MS-OXWSCONT] provides a base description of the message syntax.
[In Messages] The text that specifies the WSDL and schema might specify restrictions that reflect actual protocol behavior.

[In Messages] For example, the schema definition might allow for an element to be empty, null, or not present but the behavior of the protocol as specified restricts the same elements to being non-empty, not null, or present.
[In Transport] The SOAP version supported is SOAP 1.1, as specified in [SOAP1.1].
[In Common Message Syntax] This section contains common definitions that are used by this protocol [MS-OXWSCONT].
[In Common Message Syntax] The syntax of the definitions uses XML schema, as defined in [XMLSCHEMA1] and [XMLSCHEMA2], and Web Services Description Language (WSDL), as defined in [WSDL].
[In Namespaces] This specification [MS-OXWSCONT] defines and references various XML namespaces using the mechanisms specified in [XMLNS].

[In Namespaces] Although this specification [MS-OXWSCONT] associates a specific XML namespace prefix for each XML namespace that is used, the choice of any particular XML namespace prefix is implementation-specific and not significant for interoperability.
[In Namespaces] The Namespace URI of Prefix soap is http://schemas.xmlsoap.org/wsdl/soap/ and reference is [SOAP1.1].
[In Namespaces] The Namespace URI of Prefix tns is http://schemas.microsoft.com/exchange/services/2006/messages
[In Namespaces] The Namespace URI of Prefix xs is http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema and reference is [XMLSCHEMA2].
[In Namespaces] The Namespace URI of Prefix targetNamespace is http://schemas.microsoft.com/exchange/services/2006/messages
[In Namespaces] The Namespace URI of Prefix wsdl is http://schemas.xmlsoap.org/wsdl/ and reference is [WSDL]

[In Complex Types] t:ContactItemType(section 2.2.4.1): Represents a server contact item.

[In t:ArrayOfBinaryType Complex Type] The ArrayOfBinaryType complex type specifies a collection of certificates for a contact. <1> <xs:complexType name="ArrayOfBinaryType"> <xs:sequence> <xs:element name="Base64Binary" type="xs:base64Binary" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="unbounded" /> </xs:sequence> </xs:complexType>

[In t:ArrayOfBinaryType Complex Type] Base64Binary element: Specifies a single certificate for a contact.
[In t:ArrayOfBinaryType Complex Type] Base64Binary element: The value is encoded with base64 encoding.

[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] FileAs element: Represents how a contact is filed in the Contacts folder.
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] The type of the element of FileAsMapping is t:FileAsMappingType (section 3.1.4.1.1.2)
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] FileAsMapping element: Defines how to construct what is displayed for a contact.
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] The type of the element of DisplayName is xs:string
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] DisplayName element: Contains the display name of a contact.
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] The type of the element of GivenName is xs:string
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] GivenName element: Contains the given name for a contact.
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] The type of the element of Initials is xs:string
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] Initials element: Contains the initials for a contact.
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] The type of the element of MiddleName is xs:string
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] MiddleName element: Represents the middle name of a contact.
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] The type of the element of Nickname is xs:string
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] Nickname element: Represents the nickname of a contact.
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] The type of the element of CompleteName is t:CompleteNameType (section 3.1.4.1.2.1)
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] CompleteName element: Represents the complete name of a contact.
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] The type of the element of CompanyName is xs:string
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] CompanyName element: Contains the company name that is associated with a contact.
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] The type of the element of EmailAddresses is t:EmailAddressDictionaryType (section 3.1.4.1.2.5)
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] EmailAddress element: Contains e-mail addresses that are associated with a contact.
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] The type of the element of PhysicalAddresses is t:EmailAddressDictionaryType
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] PhysicalAddresses element: Represents a collection of physical addresses that are associated with a contact.
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] The type of the element of PhoneNumbers is t:EmailAddressDictionaryType
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] PhoneNumbers element: Represents a collection of telephone numbers for a contact.
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] The type of the element of AssistantName is xs:string
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] AssistantName element: Contains the name of the assistant for the contact.
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] The type of the element of Birthday is xs:dateTime [XMLSCHEMA2]
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] Birthday element: Represents the birthday of the contact.
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] The type of the element of BusinessHomePage is xs:anyURI [XMLSCHEMA2]
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] BusinessHomePage element: Contains the business home page Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) of a contact.
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] The type of the element of Children is t:ArrayOfStringsType ([MS-OXWSCDATA] section 2.2.4.11)
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] Children element: Contains the names of children for the contact.
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] The type of the element of Companies is t:ArrayOfStringsType.
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] Companies element: Contains the names of companies that are associated with a contact.
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] The type of the element of ContactSource is t:ContactSourceType (section 2.2.5.1)
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] ContactSource element: Describes whether the contact is located in the server store or the directory service.
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] The type of the element of Department is xs:string
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] Department element: Contains the work department for the contact.
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] The type of the element of Generation is xs:string
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] Generation element: Contains a generational abbreviation that follows the full name of a contact.
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] The type of the element of ImAddresses is t:ImAddressDictionaryType (section 3.1.4.1.2.7)
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] ImAddresses element: Contains instant messaging addresses for a contact.
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] The type of the element of JobTitle is xs:string
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] JobTitle element: Contains the job title of a contact.
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] The type of the element of Manager is xs:string
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] Manager element: Represents the manager of a contact.
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] The type of the element of Mileage is xs:string
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] Mileage element: Represents the mileage for a contact.
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] The type of the element of OfficeLocation is xs:string
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] OfficeLocation element: Represents the office location of a contact.
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] The type of the element of PostalAddressIndex is t:PhysicalAddressIndexType (section 3.1.4.1.1.5)
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] PostalAddressIndex element: Represents the index of one of the physical addresses, which is a contact's mailing address.
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] The type of the element of Profession is xs:string
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] Profession element: Represents the profession of a contact.
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] The type of the element of SpouseName is xs:string
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] SpouseName element: Represents the name of the spouse/partner of a contact.
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] The type of the element of Surname is xs:string
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] Surname element: Contains the surname of a contact.
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] The type of the element of WeddingAnniversary is xs:dateTime
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] WeddingAnniversary element: Contains the wedding anniversary date of a contact.
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] The type of the element of HasPicture is xs:boolean [XMLSCHEMA2]
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] HasPicture element: Represents that the contact has a picture.
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] The type of the element of PhoneticFullName is xs:string<2>
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] PhoneticFullName element: Contains the full name of a contact, including the first and last name, spelled phonetically.<2>
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] The type of the element of PhoneticFirstName is xs:string<2>
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] PhoneticFirstName element: Contains the first name of a contact, spelled phonetically.<2>
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] The type of the element of PhoneticLastName is xs:string<2>
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] PhoneticLastName element: Contains the last name of a contact, spelled phonetically.<2>
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] The type of the element of Alias is xs:string<2>
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] Alias element: Contains the email alias of a contact.<2>
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] The type of the element of Notes is xs:string<2>
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] Notes element: Contains supplementary contact information.<2>
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] The type of the element of Photo is xs:base64Binary [XMLSCHEMA2]<2>
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] Photo element :Contains a value that encodes the photo of a contact.<2>
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] The type of the element of UserSMIMECertificate is t:ArrayOfBinaryType (section 2.2.4.1)<2>
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] UserSMIMECertificate element: Contains a value that encodes a contact's S/MIME certificate.<2>
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] The type of the element of MSExchangeCertificate is t:ArrayOfBinaryType<2>
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] MSExchangeCertificate element: Contains a value that encodes the server certificate of a contact.<2>
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] The type of the element of DirectoryId is xs:string<2>
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] DirectoryId element: Contains the directory identifier of a contact.<2>
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] The type of the element of ManagerMailbox is t:SingleRecipientType ([MS-OXWSCDATA] section 2.2.4.60)<2>
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] ManagerMailbox element: Contains SMTP information that identifies the mailbox of a contact's manager.<2>
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] The type of the element of DirectReports is t:ArrayOfRecipientsType ([MS-OXWSCDATA] section 2.2.4.9)<2>
[In t:ContactItemType Complex Type] DirectReports element: Contains SMTP information that identifies the mailboxes of a contact's direct reports.<2>
[In Simple Types] The following table summarizes the set of common XML Schema simple type definitions [t:ContactSourceType] defined by this specification [MS-OXWSCONT].
[In Simple Types] XML Schema simple type definitions [t:ContactSourceType] that are specific to a particular operation are described with the operation.
[In Simple Types] t:ContactSourceType(section 2.2.5.1): Specifies whether a contact is located in the server database or in the directory service.
[In Simple Types] t:ContactSourceType(section 2.2.5.1): Specifies whether a distribution list is located in the server database or in the directory service.
[In t:ContactSourceType Simple Type] The ContactSourceType specifies whether a contact is located in the server database or in the directory service.
[In t:ContactSourceType Simple Type] The ContactSourceType specifies whether a distribution list is located in the server database or in the directory service.

[In t:ContactSourceType Simple Type] The type [ContactSupportType] is defined as follow:<xs:simpleType name="ContactSupportType"> <xs:restriction base="xs:string" > <xs:enumeration value="ActiveDirectory" /> <xs:enumeration value="Store" /> </xs:restriction> </xs:simpleType>
[In t:ContactSourceType Simple Type]The following values are defined by the ContactSupportType simple type: ActiveDirectory, Store.
[In t:ContactSourceType Simple Type] ActiveDirectory: Specifies that the contact is located in the directory service.
[In t:ContactSourceType Simple Type] ActiveDirectory: Specifies that the distribution list is located in the directory service.
[In t:ContactSourceType Simple Type] Store: Specifies that the contact is located in the server database.
[In t:ContactSourceType Simple Type] Store: Specifies that the distribution list is located in the server database.

[In t:ContactSourceType Simple Type] This [the ContactSupportType value] is applicable to the Contacts Web Service protocol and to the Distribution List Creation and Usage Web Service protocol [MS-OXWSDLIST].

[In t:ContactSourceType Simple Type] It [the ContactSupportType value] is also used by the ResolveNames method ([MS-OXWSRSLNM] section 3.1.4.1), returning directory and store contacts matching a search string.
[In Attributes] This specification [MS-OXWSCONT] does not define any common XML schema attribute definitions.
[In Groups] This specification [MS-OXWSCONT] does not define any common XML schema group definitions.
[In Attribute Groups] This specification [MS-OXWSCONT] does not define any common XML schema attribute group definitions.
[In Protocol Details] The client side of this protocol [MS-OXWSCONT] is simply a pass-through.
[In Protocol Details] That is, no additional timers or other state is required on the client side of this protocol [MS-OXWSCONT].

[In Protocol Details] Calls made by the higher-layer protocol or application are passed directly to the transport, and the results returned by the transport are passed directly back to the higher-layer protocol or application.
[In ExchangeServicePortType Server Details] This protocol [MS-OXWSCONT] defines a single port type. [GetItem, DeleteItem, UpdateItem, MoveItem, CopyItem, CreateItem]
[In ExchangeServicePortType Server Details] GetItem operation: Defines a request to get an item from a mailbox in the server.
[In ExchangeServicePortType Server Details] DeleteItem operation: Defines a request to delete an item from a mailbox in the server.
[In ExchangeServicePortType Server Details] UpdateItem operation: Defines a request to update an item in a mailbox.
[In ExchangeServicePortType Server Details] MoveItem operation: Defines a request to move an item in the server.
[In ExchangeServicePortType Server Details] CopyItem operation: Defines a request to copy an item in a mailbox in the server.
[In ExchangeServicePortType Server Details] CreateItem operation: Defines a request to create an item in the server.
[In Server Abstract Data Model] This protocol [MS-OXWSCONT] is a stateless protocol.

[In Server Message Processing Events and Sequencing] This protocol [MS-OXWSCONT] includes the operations listed in the following table. [GetItem, DeleteItem, UpdateItem, MoveItem, CopyItem, CreateItem]
[In Server Message Processing Events and Sequencing] GetItem operation: Gets items in the server.
[In Server Message Processing Events and Sequencing] DeleteItem operation: Deletes items in the server.
[In Server Message Processing Events and Sequencing] UpdateItem operation: Updates items in the server.
[In Server Message Processing Events and Sequencing] MoveItem operation: Moves items in the server.
[In Server Message Processing Events and Sequencing] CopyItem operation: Copies items in the server.
[In Server Message Processing Events and Sequencing] CreateItem operation: Creates items in the server.
[In GetItem] This protocol [MS-OXWSCONT] uses the GetItem operation specified in [MS-OXWSCORE] section 3.1.4.4 to get contact item elements.

[In GetItem] The following is the WSDL port type specification for the GetItem operation:<wsdl:operation name="GetItem"> <wsdl:input message="tns:GetItemSoapIn" /> <wsdl:output message="tns:GetItemSoapOut" /> </wsdl:operation>
[In GetItem] tns:GetItemSoapIn: Specifies the SOAP message that defines the contact item to get.

[In GetItem] tns:GetItemSoapIn: The Items ([MS-OXWSCDATA] section 2.2.4.42) child element of the GetItem ([MS-OXWSCORE] section 3.1.4.4.2.1) child element that specifies the XML request MUST contain the following elements: t:ItemResponseShapeType ([MS-OXWSCDATA] section 2.2.4.38), t:ItemIdType ([MS-OXWSCORE] section 2.2.4.19).
[In GetItem] tns:GetItemSoapIn: All other elements MUST be empty.
[In GetItem] tns:GetItemSoapOut: Specifies the SOAP message returned by the server in response.
[In GetItem] tns:GetItemSoapOut: The server returns a t:ItemResponseShapeType ([MS-OXWSCDATA] section 2.2.4.38) element that contains properties associated with the distribution list item.
[In Simple Types] The following XML schema simple type definitions are specific to this operation.
[In t:EmailAddressKeyType Simple Type] The EmailAddressKeyType simple type represents a way to identify a single e-mail address within the e-mail address collection for a contact.

[In t:EmailAddressKeyType Simple Type] The type [EmailAddressKeyType] is defined as follow: <xs:simpleType name="EmailAddressKeyType"> <xs:restriction base="xs:string" > <xs:enumeration value="EmailAddress1" /> <xs:enumeration value="EmailAddress2" /> <xs:enumeration value="EmailAddress3" /> </xs:restriction> </xs:simpleType>
[In t:EmailAddressKeyType Simple Type] The following values are defined by the EmailAddressKeyType simple type: [EmailAddress1, EmailAddress2, EmailAddress3]
[In t:EmailAddressKeyType Simple Type] EmailAddress1: Identifies the first e-mail address for the contact.
[In t:EmailAddressKeyType Simple Type] EmailAddress2: Identifies the second e-mail address for the contact.
[In t:EmailAddressKeyType Simple Type] EmailAddress3: Identifies the third e-mail address for the contact.
[In t:FileAsMappingType Simple Type] The FileAsMappingType simple type defines how to construct what is displayed for a contact in the FileAs property.

[In t:FileAsMappingType Simple Type] The type [FileAsMappingType] is defined as follow: <xs:simpleType name="FileAsMappingType"> <xs:restriction base="xs:string" > <xs:enumeration value="None" /> <xs:enumeration value="LastCommaFirst" /> <xs:enumeration value="FirstSpaceLast" /> <xs:enumeration value="Company" /> <xs:enumeration value="LastCommaFirstCompany" /> <xs:enumeration value="CompanyLastFirst" /> <xs:enumeration value="LastFirst" /> <xs:enumeration value="LastFirstCompany" /> <xs:enumeration value="CompanyLastCommaFirst" /> <xs:enumeration value="LastFirstSuffix" /> <xs:enumeration value="LastSpaceFirstCompany" /> <xs:enumeration value="CompanyLastSpaceFirst" /> <xs:enumeration value="LastSpaceFirst" /> <xs:enumeration value="DisplayName" /> <xs:enumeration value="FirstName" /> <xs:enumeration value="LastFirstMiddleSuffix" /> <xs:enumeration value="LastName" /> <xs:enumeration value="Empty" /> </xs:restriction> </xs:simpleType>

[In t:FileAsMappingType Simple Type] The following values are defined by the FileAsMappingType simple type: [None, LastCommaFirst, FirstSpaceLast, Company, LastCommaFirstCompany, CompanyLastFirst, LastFirst, LastFirstCompany, CompanyLastCommaFirst, LastFirstSuffix, LastSpaceFirstCompany, CompanyLastSpaceFirst, LastSpaceFirst, DisplayName, FirstName, LastFirstMiddleSuffix, LastName, Empty]
[In t:FileAsMappingType Simple Type] None: Indicates that the FileAs value is not constructed from other contact's properties, but is represented by a string, saved "as is".
[In t:FileAsMappingType Simple Type] LastCommaFirst: Indicates that the contact is displayed as the last name followed by a comma and the first name.
[In t:FileAsMappingType Simple Type] FirstSpaceLast: Indicates that the contact is displayed as the first name followed by a space and the last name.
[In t:FileAsMappingType Simple Type] Company: Indicates that the company name is displayed.
[In t:FileAsMappingType Simple Type] LastCommaFirstCompany: Indicates that the contact is displayed as the last name, a comma, the first name, and the company name.
[In t:FileAsMappingType Simple Type] CompanyLastFirst: Indicates that the contact is displayed as the company name, the last name, and the first name.
[In t:FileAsMappingType Simple Type] LastFirst: Indicates that the contact is displayed as the last name followed by the first name.
[In t:FileAsMappingType Simple Type] LastFirstCompany: Indicates that the contact is displayed as the last name, the first name, and the company name.
[In t:FileAsMappingType Simple Type] CompanyLastCommaFirst: Indicates that the contact is displayed as the company name, the last name, a comma, and the first name.
[In t:FileAsMappingType Simple Type] LastFirstSuffix: Indicates that the contact is displayed as the last name, the first name, and the suffix for the contact.
[In t:FileAsMappingType Simple Type] LastSpaceFirstCompany: Indicates that the contact is displayed as the last name, a space, the first name, and the company name.
[In t:FileAsMappingType Simple Type] CompanyLastSpaceFirst: Indicates that the contact is displayed as the company name, the last name, a space, and the first name.
[In t:FileAsMappingType Simple Type] LastSpaceFirst: Indicates that the contact is displayed as the last name, followed by a space and the first name.
[In t:FileAsMappingType Simple Type] DisplayName: Indicates that the contact is displayed as the display name.
[In t:FileAsMappingType Simple Type] FirstName: Indicates that the contact is displayed as the first name.
[In t:FileAsMappingType Simple Type] LastFirstMiddleSuffix: Indicates that the contact is displayed as the last name, the first name, the middle name, and the suffix for the contact.
[In t:FileAsMappingType Simple Type] LastName: Indicates that the contact is displayed as the last name.
[In t:FileAsMappingType Simple Type] Empty: Indicates that the contact is displayed as empty.
[In t:ImAddressKeyType Simple Type] The ImAddressKeyType enumeration represents the instant messaging addresses for a contact.

[In t:ImAddressKeyType Simple Type] The type [ImAddressKeyType] is defined as follow: <xs:simpleType name="ImAddressKeyType"> <xs:restriction base="xs:string" > <xs:enumeration value="ImAddress1" /> <xs:enumeration value="ImAddress2" /> <xs:enumeration value="ImAddress3" /> </xs:restriction> </xs:simpleType>
[In t:ImAddressKeyType Simple Type] The following values are defined by the ImAddressKeyType simple type: [ImAddress1, ImAddress2, ImAddress3]
[In t:ImAddressKeyType Simple Type] ImAddress1: Identifies the first instant messaging address for the user.
[In t:ImAddressKeyType Simple Type] ImAddress2: Identifies the second instant messaging address for the user.
[In t:ImAddressKeyType Simple Type] ImAddress3: Identifies the third instant messaging address for the user.
